---
layout: article
title: Map a pricing tier to project config
description: Translate a customer's plan into enforceable project limits and gated services with the Project API.
---

Underneath the marketing, a pricing tier is a set of limits: Free gets a small ceiling, paid plans lift it. You could enforce those limits in your own code on every request, but then your backend carries logic that Appwrite can carry for you. The Project API lets you stamp the limits straight onto the customer's project, so Appwrite turns away the over-quota sign-up or the too-long session on its own, and your code stays out of the loop.

This journey configures a Free tier as the worked example:

- A small user cap.
- Tight session rules.
- Functions held back for paid plans.

When a customer upgrades, you run the same calls with the higher numbers, which is why it pays to keep one function per tier.

{% info title="Required scopes" %}
The policy calls need the `project.policies.write` scope, and the service call needs the `project.write` scope.
{% /info %}

# Cap the number of users {% #user-limit %}

Free tiers almost always cap how many users a project can hold. Set up the client, then set that ceiling, and Appwrite refuses sign-ups past it until the customer upgrades or you raise the number.

{% multicode %}
```server-nodejs
import { Client, Project } from 'node-appwrite';

const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('<PROJECT_ID>')
    .setKey('<YOUR_API_KEY>');

const project = new Project(client);

const result = await project.updateUserLimitPolicy({
    total: 100
});
```
```server-deno
import { Client, Project } from "npm:node-appwrite";

const client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('<PROJECT_ID>')
    .setKey('<YOUR_API_KEY>');

const project = new Project(client);

const result = await project.updateUserLimitPolicy({
    total: 100
});
```
```server-php
<?php

use Appwrite\Client;
use Appwrite\Services\Project;

$client = new Client();

$client
    ->setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    ->setProject('<PROJECT_ID>')
    ->setKey('<YOUR_API_KEY>');

$project = new Project($client);

$result = $project->updateUserLimitPolicy(
    total: 100
);
```
```server-python
from appwrite.client import Client
from appwrite.services.project import Project

client = Client()
client.set_endpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
client.set_project('<PROJECT_ID>')
client.set_key('<YOUR_API_KEY>')

project = Project(client)

result = project.update_user_limit_policy(
    total = 100
)
```
```server-ruby
require 'appwrite'

include Appwrite

client = Client.new
    .set_endpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .set_project('<PROJECT_ID>')
    .set_key('<YOUR_API_KEY>')

project = Project.new(client)

response = project.update_user_limit_policy(
    total: 100
)
```
```server-dotnet
using Appwrite;
using Appwrite.Services;

Client client = new Client()
    .SetEndPoint("https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1")
    .SetProject("<PROJECT_ID>")
    .SetKey("<YOUR_API_KEY>");

Project project = new Project(client);

var result = await project.UpdateUserLimitPolicy(
    total: 100
);
```
```server-dart
import 'package:dart_appwrite/dart_appwrite.dart';

Client client = Client()
    .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
    .setProject('<PROJECT_ID>')
    .setKey('<YOUR_API_KEY>');

Project project = Project(client);

final result = await project.updateUserLimitPolicy(
    total: 100,
);
```
```server-kotlin
import io.appwrite.Client
import io.appwrite.services.Project

val client = Client()
    .setEndpoint("https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1")
    .setProject("<PROJECT_ID>")
    .setKey("<YOUR_API_KEY>")

val project = Project(client)

val response = project.updateUserLimitPolicy(
    total = 100
)
```
```server-java
import io.appwrite.Client;
import io.appwrite.coroutines.CoroutineCallback;
import io.appwrite.services.Project;

Client client = new Client()
    .setEndpoint("https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1")
    .setProject("<PROJECT_ID>")
    .setKey("<YOUR_API_KEY>");

Project project = new Project(client);

project.updateUserLimitPolicy(
    100, // total
    new CoroutineCallback<>((result, error) -> {
        if (error != null) {
            error.printStackTrace();
            return;
        }
        System.out.println(result);
    })
);
```
```server-swift
import Appwrite

let client = Client()
    .setEndpoint("https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1")
    .setProject("<PROJECT_ID>")
    .setKey("<YOUR_API_KEY>")

let project = Project(client)

let result = try await project.updateUserLimitPolicy(
    total: 100
)
```
```server-go
package main

import (
    "fmt"
    "github.com/appwrite/sdk-for-go/appwrite"
)

func main() {
    client := appwrite.NewClient(
        appwrite.WithEndpoint("https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1"),
        appwrite.WithProject("<PROJECT_ID>"),
        appwrite.WithKey("<YOUR_API_KEY>"),
    )

    service := appwrite.NewProject(client)
    result, err := service.UpdateUserLimitPolicy(100)

    if err != nil {
        panic(err)
    }

    fmt.Println(result)
}
```
```server-rust
use appwrite::Client;
use appwrite::services::project::Project;

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    let client = Client::new()
        .set_endpoint("https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1")
        .set_project("<PROJECT_ID>")
        .set_key("<YOUR_API_KEY>");

    let project = Project::new(&client);

    let result = project.update_user_limit_policy(100).await?;

    println!("{:?}", result);
    Ok(())
}
```
```bash
appwrite project update-user-limit-policy \
    --total 100
```
```http
PATCH /v1/project/policies/user-limit HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
X-Appwrite-Project: <PROJECT_ID>
X-Appwrite-Key: <YOUR_API_KEY>

{
  "total": 100
}
```
{% /multicode %}

On your top tier, pass `null` to lift the cap entirely.

# Limit concurrent sessions {% #session-limit %}

Cap how many sessions a single user can hold at once, so a shared Free login cannot quietly serve a whole office from one seat.

{% multicode %}
```server-nodejs
const result = await project.updateSessionLimitPolicy({
    total: 3
});
```
```server-deno
const result = await project.updateSessionLimitPolicy({
    total: 3
});
```
```server-php
$result = $project->updateSessionLimitPolicy(
    total: 3
);
```
```server-python
result = project.update_session_limit_policy(
    total = 3
)
```
```server-ruby
response = project.update_session_limit_policy(
    total: 3
)
```
```server-dotnet
var result = await project.UpdateSessionLimitPolicy(
    total: 3
);
```
```server-dart
final result = await project.updateSessionLimitPolicy(
    total: 3,
);
```
```server-kotlin
val response = project.updateSessionLimitPolicy(
    total = 3
)
```
```server-java
project.updateSessionLimitPolicy(
    3, // total
    new CoroutineCallback<>((result, error) -> {
        if (error != null) {
            error.printStackTrace();
            return;
        }
        System.out.println(result);
    })
);
```
```server-swift
let result = try await project.updateSessionLimitPolicy(
    total: 3
)
```
```server-go
