```http
PATCH /v1/project/policies/session-limit HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
X-Appwrite-Project: <PROJECT_ID>
X-Appwrite-Key: <YOUR_API_KEY>

{
  "total": 3
}
```
{% /multicode %}

# Set the session lifetime {% #session-duration %}

Set how long a session stays valid before the user has to authenticate again. A shorter window on Free, a longer one as customers pay for the convenience of staying logged in. This example is seven days, in seconds.

{% multicode %}
```server-nodejs
const result = await project.updateSessionDurationPolicy({
    duration: 604800
});
```
```server-deno
const result = await project.updateSessionDurationPolicy({
    duration: 604800
});
```
```server-php
$result = $project->updateSessionDurationPolicy(
    duration: 604800
);
```
```server-python
result = project.update_session_duration_policy(
    duration = 604800
)
```
```server-ruby
response = project.update_session_duration_policy(
    duration: 604800
)
```
```server-dotnet
var result = await project.UpdateSessionDurationPolicy(
    duration: 604800
);
```
```server-dart
final result = await project.updateSessionDurationPolicy(
    duration: 604800,
);
```
```server-kotlin
val response = project.updateSessionDurationPolicy(
    duration = 604800
)
```
```server-java
project.updateSessionDurationPolicy(
    604800, // duration
    new CoroutineCallback<>((result, error) -> {
        if (error != null) {
            error.printStackTrace();
            return;
        }
        System.out.println(result);
    })
);
```
```server-swift
let result = try await project.updateSessionDurationPolicy(
    duration: 604800
)
```
```server-go
result, err := service.UpdateSessionDurationPolicy(604800)

if err != nil {
    panic(err)
}

fmt.Println(result)
```
```server-rust
let result = project.update_session_duration_policy(604800).await?;

println!("{:?}", result);
```
```bash
appwrite project update-session-duration-policy \
    --duration 604800
```
```http
PATCH /v1/project/policies/session-duration HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
X-Appwrite-Project: <PROJECT_ID>
X-Appwrite-Key: <YOUR_API_KEY>

{
  "duration": 604800
}
```
{% /multicode %}

# Gate a service behind a tier {% #gate-service %}

Some features belong only to customers who pay. Take Functions off the Free tier's client API and their app cannot invoke a function until they move up a plan.

{% multicode %}
```server-nodejs
const result = await project.updateService({
    serviceId: ProjectServiceId.Functions,
    enabled: false
});
```
```server-deno
const result = await project.updateService({
    serviceId: ProjectServiceId.Functions,
    enabled: false
});
```
```server-php
$result = $project->updateService(
    serviceId: ProjectServiceId::FUNCTIONS(),
    enabled: false
);
```
```server-python
result = project.update_service(
    service_id = ProjectServiceId.FUNCTIONS,
    enabled = False
)
```
```server-ruby
response = project.update_service(
    service_id: ProjectServiceId::FUNCTIONS,
    enabled: false
)
```
```server-dotnet
var result = await project.UpdateService(
    serviceId: ProjectServiceId.Functions,
    enabled: false
);
```
```server-dart
final result = await project.updateService(
    serviceId: enums.ProjectServiceId.functions,
    enabled: false,
);
```
```server-kotlin
val response = project.updateService(
    serviceId = ProjectServiceId.FUNCTIONS,
    enabled = false
)
```
```server-java
project.updateService(
    ProjectServiceId.FUNCTIONS, // serviceId
    false, // enabled
    new CoroutineCallback<>((result, error) -> {
        if (error != null) {
            error.printStackTrace();
            return;
        }
        System.out.println(result);
    })
);
```
```server-swift
let result = try await project.updateService(
    serviceId: .functions,
    enabled: false
)
```
```server-go
result, err := service.UpdateService(
    "functions",
    false,
)

if err != nil {
    panic(err)
}

fmt.Println(result)
```
```server-rust
let result = project.update_service(
    ProjectServiceId::Functions,
    false,
).await?;

println!("{:?}", result);
```
```bash
appwrite project update-service \
    --service-id functions \
    --enabled false
```
```http
PATCH /v1/project/services/functions HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
X-Appwrite-Project: <PROJECT_ID>
X-Appwrite-Key: <YOUR_API_KEY>

{
  "enabled": false
}
```
{% /multicode %}

{% info title="Service gating affects client access only" %}
Disabling a service removes it from the client-facing API only. A Server SDK using an API key still reaches it, so service gating controls what a customer's app can call. Enforce billing entitlements in your own backend.
{% /info %}

# Next steps {% #next-steps %}

Group these calls into one function per tier and a plan change becomes a single call against the customer's project, with Appwrite enforcing the limits from then on. From here:

- [Provision a project's baseline](/docs/partners/project/provisioning) and apply the tier as part of onboarding.
- Read the [Policies](/docs/partners/project/policies) reference for the other limits you can enforce.
